As a lifelong vegetarian, I have thoroughly enjoyed visiting Harmony Cafe over the last 25ish years. I would literally fly to DC just for their vegetarian hot and sour soup. Even in my current city, I can’t get veggie “meats” like they do it. Nothing has ever been better. I have been to China (and had amazing Buddhist vegetarian) and all over the world, and this is easily in the top TWO Chinese vegetarian/vegan restaurants I’ve ever been to. I would often order 6 or 8 hot and sour soups to freeze some for when I had a cold or just wanted a piece of “home”. Keep this place open so I have somewhere to get fried tofu and vege soup that blows my mind. Be patient with service and be rewarded with awesomeness.
Probably the best vegetarian Chinese food in the DC area. I eat meat but get vegetarian food every time!! Recommend the tangy tofu!
So good!
Horrible experience. Too much to list.

Sketchy entrance and menu, but vegetarian dishes are actually good. Only one server, but was nice and working hard unlike other chinese places. Not super authentic; however, vegetarian meat tasted like real meat which is rare to find. Downsides are the place is small and egg drop soup is the worst i ever had.

Harmony Cafe is one of my favorite places to eat in Georgetown. Once you walk down the stairs you're greeted by a wonderful hostess and a fantastic selection of traditional and familiar dishes. And at a great price!
Food quality was poor, service was subpar, but at least they kept filling my glass of water
Surprised us with one of the best vegan/vegetarian menus in D.C. for an Asian restaurant. Lots of really delicious mock meats! Kind of hidden but well worth stopping into if you're in Georgetown.

Hidden little gem. All three dishes that were ordered had great flavoring: sweet and sour chicken, combination fried rice, and lo mein. The dishes came out super hot in temperature. The decor was really cool, you have to pay attention to the details. And the server was really nice. Definitely a place to be a regular at.

Great food and great service. I wish we had a great Chinese spot like this in Adams Morgan being that the last good spot we had (Wok N Roll) got ran out due to the outrageous unaffordable rent raise sadly... Anyhow I was so happy to come out to Georgetown last night and indulge in their beef satay sticks ( Teriyaki and Malaysian), shrimp spring rolls and curry chicken fried rice. The food and service here is superb along with the lavish Asian ambiance (feng shui).
Very polite and friendly, came back for a second time and was greeted with a smile. She even  remembered that my wife and I do not eat a particular food. Most definitely would return and recommend!
Great food at decent price. Nice quiet ambience

The food was better than we expected.  Not too pricey.  We ordered Singapore fried rice vermicelli and other noodles.  Not totally authentic but still tasted good.  The staff was friendly and the place was clean including the washroom.  Would visit and eat there again.
Love this place.  The veggie meat is so good.
Great atmosphere and service! Crab dip was gooooood!

One of the only places you'll find veggie meat Chinese dishes in the DC area. Considering this is in Georgetown, prices are very fair-- our total for 2 entrees and an appetizer post-tax was about $22. I'll definitely go again.

I have quite a few allergies that I wanted to talk to the waitress about, but I didn't have the energy when I went to work the potential language barrier. I did my best to order on my own and just let her know I was allergic to eggs (my most severe allergy) which was difficult enough. I ordered a curry pot and was surprised at the color when I received and after a few bites in it was NOT what I ordered. It was still pretty good so I decided not to exchange it, but am still frustrated; I even pointed at the menu. I'm intrigued by this place so I'll return again. They appear to be pretty gluten-free, vegetarian, and vegan friendly with lots of veggie "meat" options on their menu.
Very tasty food. restaurant is quiet and relaxing.
This is a fantastic small restaurant. The food is amazing and the decor is beautiful. Too beautiful and wonderful for photos. You must experience this restaurant for yourself.

Never been treated so rudely before. From the moment I said I wanted to place a to go order. She acted like it was the most inconvenient thing in the world. Went from take long long time to 30 maybe 40 minutes. Only one other party in dinning room that hadn't been served yet. Ridiculous! Will see if food makes up for terrible customer service

This place is a hidden gem for great food in DC. I've visited this place twice now and both times (to my surprise) my girlfriend and I had the place all to ourselves. Both times I got two different salmon dishes (salmon is my favorite) and both dishes were fantastic. The service impeccable, the staff is friendly and super accommodating. Couldn't have been happier with my experience here and probably my favorite Chinese restaurant I've been too so far in DC. I really hope this place sees more business. Highly recommended.

I really love this place! You can have a great inexpensive lunchwith faux chicken & beef options.You will have to walk downstairs, though. Nice decor,also.

Perfect for a nice quick dinner before a movie! Looks like a Chinese dinner spot from the 90s, very nostalgic. Love the Gold Buddha decor. Squeaky clean. Get the jasmine tea and open your fortune cookie! I got steamed vegs with steamed tofu and rice with a dash of soy sauce. Perfect!

The toilet paper really made the meal. Usually restraunts cheap out on the paper, but Its CHARMIN ULTRASOFT, make sure to not go anywhere else besides here. This place is delicious, especially as a vegetarian. Everything they have can be made vegetarian with really good meat substitutes, so I always go for the pork fried rice.

I dig this place. It’s a hole in the wall ( underground) Chinese place in Georgetown that is very vegan friendly. You can have Vegan wonton soup here! I haven’t had wontons in forever! It’s a quick walk over the bridge if you’re coming from VA. You can get in and out pretty quickly. I had the Mongolian/ curry chow fun and it was goood.

True hidden gem!  I've lived here over three years and never knew this place existed.  Super quiet relaxing lower level restaurant with a completely vegetarian friendly menu and amazing prices plus service in the heart of Georgetown.  Highly recommend for dine in or takeout.

Very amazing Chinese vegetarian food, must go to if you are in a Washington DC. Very quiet though, if 7pm is rush hour, then that’s not very good as there were only 2 other people in the restaurant! Very cosy and cost effective - amazing food.. definitely underrated!

Lovely space, quiet, good food. We had Boo Boo chicken appetizer (spicy and good), oriental chicken salad (friend reported as good), a green bean dish (yummy), a tofu dish (very good) and plenty of cold iced water on a hot day.

I have been coming here since 1999. You can still get a glass of wine for $3.50 and appetizers for $5. The shitake mushroom appetizer is still very yummy, and their extensive menu should satisfy the meat eater, noodle or rice lover, or vegetarian in you.
Good place for Chinese food, recommend a Tsingtao for a meal. Goes good with everything. Also the value here is amazing, the shiitake mushrooms are the best.

Love their vegan dishes.
fly in my noodles :(

Atmosphere is great and a welcomed break from the rest of Georgetown. There could be a full blown riot on M street, and you wouldn't know because you'd be having a quiet and cozy meal in this basement restaurant. I've been coming to this place for 15 years and nothing has changed. NOTHING. For 15 years there has always been the same hostess/waitress, and I'm pretty sure the music is just one song on repeat. It's the best. In a town that looks nothing like it did 15 years ago, this place keeps it real and hasn't tried to turn their food selection into some asian fusion tapas BS like every other top chef place in DC. If you don't like this kind of vibe, then go somewhere else.  I'm vegetarian and I love going to chinese places with fake meat options and this place has plenty. The food here won't blow your mind, but it's always been solid and I've never been let down. The price is right and you won't leave with an empt stomach.
Try the vegan beef!

Good location. Beautiful environment. Delicious food. Inexpensive price. Very friendly to children. Nice service. The waitress/hostess smiled beautifully all the time. The restaurant didn't have highchair so we used our stroller for our baby to eat, which worked out fine. I was very sorry for the food and mess our baby left on the floor, but the waitress/hostess told me "it is ok" with a big smile. :)
Good food! Great flavor
Good tasty selection of vegeterian food at reasonable price.

The only thing good was the sweet waitress.  The hot and sour soup tasted like a gummy mix: it was just tofu and mung beans in a gooey broth. The shrimp in the spring rolls was going bad. The beef and snow peas tasted like a bad TV dinner; it was more akin to frozen pot roast with vegetables. There was NO distinct flavor whatsoever. Atmosphere is rustic and cozy and, again, the waitress was quite welcoming. But the food was terrible.

Before I had a child the place was ok. However upon bringing my wife & new son to the place from Utah, I found the experience to he horrible. To begin with they have child seats at all. So you either have to hold your child while you try to eat yourself, or put your child in inappropriately & dangerously large adult seat.  We went there twice in November with our son. The first time we used a could of chairs from an unused table to corral our toddler - so that we could eat and have him not walking everywhere. This worked pretty well. The second time we went we tried this again. However this time the woman waitress told us that we could not use chairs from an adjoining table even though it was not being used.  We walked out at this point.  I called back and spoke with the man-chef (the owner?). The man refused to hear me out. He hung up on me quickly before I could finish a sentence or give a full response.  Discrimination against people with children. That is what is going on at this place. They don't want people with children to show up.  If you were ever a child yourself, or if you have had children, I suggest you avoid Harmony Cafe at all costs. There is only "harmony" at Harmony Cafe when you don't show up with your flesh & blood children. That's not real harmony, nor are such actions consistent which Buddhist philosophy.  No we were not letting our son run everywhere in the place. We were trying to avoid that & to corral him using a couple of chairs so that we ourselves could eat. The staff refused to allow this, and they hung up on us when we called to complain.  FYI a more laid back & friendly alternative is just across the river (TNR Cafe is Rosslyn). TNR by comparison has child seats, is more friendly, and it's similarly fairly quiet.

I went here with a friend for dinner. The place was very cute, in a basement on M street, and seemed much bigger than it was. Food was delicious and cheap, and brought by a very nice and friendly waitress. The cold sesame noodles were definitely my favorite entree, not the best I'd ever had, but damn good.

Seriously the best chinese food ever! I live in California now but miss this place on a regular basis. If you haven't already try the crispy shiitake mushrooms, I haven't been able to find anything that comes close to them anywhere.
i really enjoyed this restaurant and the atmosphere was very nice. service was friendly and they liked to get to know the people there. i really lilke getting a frozen drink or a snack there!
Very nice place, very reasonable prices, great food.
